aV\u000aChadwick Boseman definitely feels the vibe that was James Brown in \u201cGet On Up.\u201d\u000aHard to imagine anyone else in the role of singer James Brown than actor Chadwick Boseman.
p1322
aVHe nails it.
p1323
aVBozeman rises above the material in \u201cGet On Up,\u201d now in its home entertainment release.
p1324
aVYou may not like the way the story is presented, but you can certainly appreciate the talent involved.
p1325
aVThe hardest working man in show business lived a complicated life, but that was no reason to make his story hard to follow.
p1326
aVThe screenplay bounces like a ping-pong ball from childhood to prison to manhood to early showbiz to late showbiz to Brown\u2019s mental problems.
p1327
aVIt makes you want to scream out for a more linear approach.
p1328
aVThere\u2019s nothing wrong with flashbacks and flash forwards.
p1329
aVMost movies use at least a flashback or two to help tell their stories.
p1330
aVBut, \u201cGet On Up\u201d turns Brown\u2019s life into popcorn.
p1331
aVIt\u2019s like catching the kernels as they jump out of the pan.
p1332
aVUnless you\u2019re already familiar with the singer\u2019s life, it\u2019s confusing.
p1333
aVSo many people were a part of this man\u2019s history.
p1334
aVIt deserved a better telling.
p1335
aVSo, let\u2019s cover the positive.
p1336
aVBoseman.
p1337
aVThe guy has talent, and it\u2019s on display.
p1338
aVHe captures Brown from start to finish.
p1339
aVFrom his early convictions that he could be something special to the excesses of super-stardom.
p1340
aVBozeman shows us the doubts, the confidence, the flamboyance, the regrets and the talent (including some amazing dance moves) that made Brown a living legend.
p1341
aVThe story doesn\u2019t give us much about Brown\u2019s political activism, although it shows him convincing the mayor of Boston that he should allow Brown\u2019s concert to go ahead shortly after the Reverend Martin Luther King, Jr.\u2019s assassination.
p1342
aVIt also shows that very concert getting out of hand and how Brown brought things back under control.
p1343
aVThe supporting cast in \u201cGet On Up\u201d is excellent, especially a small scene with Brandon Mychal Smith as Little Richard.
p1344
aVNow, I\u2019m ready to see Little Richard\u2019s story.
p1345
aVLike Boseman, Smith carried the role.
p1346
aVYou may not like the way the story is presented, but \u201cGet On Up\u201d gives you insights into Brown\u2019s life.
p1347
aVIt\u2019s worth the time of anyone who loves the Godfather of Soul.
p1348
